Fst Analysis

Cleaning the workspace

rm(list=ls())

Calling the Required Packages

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

Loading the data from the local Computer

fst <- read.table(file="/home/gill/Project_2022/PCA_analysis/RUS_EUR_Window.windowed.weir.fst", sep="\t",header=TRUE)
fst$index <- 1:nrow(fst)

Calculating the Threshold and adding the Outlier Column to the Data

my_threshold <- quantile(fst$WEIGHTED_FST, c(0.975,0.995,0.9999),na.rm=TRUE)
fst <- fst %>% mutate(outlier = ifelse(fst$WEIGHTED_FST > my_threshold[1], "outlier", "background"))

Dividing and Subsetting the Loci based on their Fst Value in weak, Medium, high using the threshold values from quantile

tallied_data <- fst %>% group_by(outlier) %>% tally()
weak <- fst[fst$WEIGHTED_FST > my_threshold[1],]
medium <- fst[fst$WEIGHTED_FST > my_threshold[2],]
high <- fst[fst$WEIGHTED_FST > my_threshold[3],]

Checking the Normality Hypothesis of the Fst Values

ggplot(fst ,aes(x=fst$WEIGHTED_FST)) + geom_density()

q_normal <- rnorm(nrow(fst),-0.0006727742,0.05736008)
qqplot(q_normal,fst$WEIGHTED_FST)

mean(fst$WEIGHTED_FST)
## [1] 0.003403367
sd(fst$WEIGHTED_FST)
## [1] 0.01787492
m <- ggplot(fst,aes(sample=WEIGHTED_FST))+stat_qq()+stat_qq_line()
m

### Plotting the Fst table

k <- ggplot(fst,aes(index, fst$WEIGHTED_FST,color=CHROM,shape=outlier))+geom_point()+xlab("Nucleotide Location")+ylab("Weighted Fst")
k
